# Supabase — Connections & Supavisor Reference

> This is the #1 cause of confusing production errors in Rocket projects on Netlify.
> Serverless = always use port 6543 (transaction mode). Never port 5432 in production.

---

## The Two Connection Modes

| | Session mode | Transaction mode |
|---|---|---|
| Port | 5432 | 6543 |
| Use for | Long-lived processes (local dev, migrations, Prisma shadow DB) | Serverless functions (Netlify, Vercel, Edge) |
| Persistent connection | Yes | No — new connection per transaction |
| Prepared statements | Supported | NOT supported — must disable |
| pg_cron, triggers | Works | Works |
| Supabase CLI / migrations | Must use 5432 | — |

### Connection strings — where to find them
```
Supabase Dashboard → Settings → Database → Connection string

Session mode (port 5432):
postgresql://postgres:[PASSWORD]@db.[PROJECT_REF].supabase.co:5432/postgres

Transaction mode / Supavisor (port 6543):
postgresql://postgres.[PROJECT_REF]:[PASSWORD]@aws-0-[REGION].pooler.supabase.com:6543/postgres
```

---

## Netlify / Serverless Rule

Every Next.js API route on Netlify is a serverless function. Each invocation:
- Gets a new process
- Cannot hold a persistent database connection
- Must use transaction mode (port 6543)

```bash
# .env — for Drizzle / Prisma in Netlify deployment
DATABASE_URL="postgresql://postgres.[REF]:[PASSWORD]@aws-0-[REGION].pooler.supabase.com:6543/postgres"

# Local migrations only (use direct connection for CLI)
DIRECT_URL="postgresql://postgres:[PASSWORD]@db.[REF].supabase.co:5432/postgres"
```

---

## Connection Limits by Compute Tier

| Compute tier | Max connections | Recommended pool size |
|---|---|---|
| Nano / Free | 60 | 10 |
| Micro | 60 | 10 |
| Small | 90 | 15 |
| Medium | 120 | 20 |
| Large | 160 | 25 |
| XL | 240 | 35 |

Supavisor itself uses ~3–5 connections from your quota.
supabase-js (anon/service_role) uses the REST API — does NOT consume database connections directly.
Direct PostgreSQL connections (Drizzle, Prisma, pg) DO consume connections.

